      "writtenOn": "2018-11-07T03:35:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "OK, I got the infra/bots/assets/skimage/download.py script to work, and I have three folders. But I can\u0027t get any numbers from nanobench:\n\n```\n$ ls ~/etc/nanobench/ | head\n01_original.jpg\n122224874ic_lockscreen_emergencycall_pressed.png\n1.bmp\n2014_dog.png\nartificial.jpg\nart.jpg\nbattery_charge_background.png\nBH_LMC.png\nblast.gif\ndesk_yahoonews_0.jpg\n\n$ out/rel/nanobench --images ~/etc/nanobench/ --match Codec\nTimer overhead: 20.9ns\ncurr/maxrss\tloops\tmin\tmedian\tmean\tmax\tstddev\tsamples   \tconfig\tbench\n```\n\nIs \"--match Codec\" right??",
      "parentUuid": "95a05d97_bd9152c0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 13,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 13,
        "endChar": 17
